1
00:00:02,030 --> 00:00:03,840
Even if I'm in love with you,

2
00:00:07,910 --> 00:00:09,980
please don't fall for me.

3
00:00:31,180 --> 00:00:33,180
I honestly have no idea
what you're talking about.

4
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:36,910
And besides,

5
00:00:37,030 --> 00:00:38,996
you've been acting weird
for a while now, haven't you?

6
00:00:39,020 --> 00:00:40,260
You tell me you like me,

7
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:41,670
and then what?

8
00:00:42,060 --> 00:00:43,770
You tell me not to like you back?

9
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:45,920
And what was that other thing?

10
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,540
Not wanting to be a "stain" on my life?

11
00:00:50,126 --> 00:00:51,366
I don't give a damn about that.

12
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,330
You're selling yourself way too short.

13
00:00:58,480 --> 00:01:00,040
I don't want you to be in pain

14
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:02,600
just because you're with me.

15
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:07,440
Akira, I care about you,

16
00:01:08,210 --> 00:01:10,050
way more than you can imagine.

17
00:01:20,650 --> 00:01:21,650
So,

18
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,540
just be straight with me.

19
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:28,700
Why do you keep trying to shut me out?

20
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:32,150
It seems like...

21
00:01:33,350 --> 00:01:35,940
you're still hung up on
something from middle school.

22
00:01:36,420 --> 00:01:37,700
What exactly happened back then?

23
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:48,600
No matter what happened in your past,

24
00:01:48,690 --> 00:01:50,690
there's no way I could ever hate you.

25
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,560
But...

26
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:08,860
this has nothing to do with you, Kanata.

27
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:14,110
Then stop saying you like me.

28
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,520
If you're not even brave
enough to tell me why,

29
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:18,190
then stop trying to control how I feel.

30
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,200
When it comes to us...

31
00:02:24,730 --> 00:02:26,810
you don't get to make all
the decisions on your own.

32
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:32,790
Are you really just going to give up

33
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,090
on our future without even trying?

34
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:48,000
"Contrast"

35
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:52,700
(Episode 7: Holding Back)

36
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,999
(Yoichi: Something came up, so I might be
a bit late. I'll text you when I'm there.)

37
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,000
(Akira: Got it.)

38
00:04:02,001 --> 00:04:05,041
(Yoichi: So, how are things with him?
If you need to talk, I'm always here.)

39
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,740
Who's really leaning on who here...?

40
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:17,060
Yoichi!

41
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:23,490
Welcome back.

42
00:04:23,491 --> 00:04:24,570
Long time no see!

43
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:27,390
Let's go.

44
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:36,580
So,

45
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,420
how long is that internship for?

46
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:43,610
I applied for the long-term
one, so about a month.

47
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,920
I see.

48
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,639
But since you're finally back,

49
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,400
aren't you going to visit home?

50
00:04:52,910 --> 00:04:53,910
Even if I did,

51
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:55,750
there's not much for me to do there.

52
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,420
What about Akira?

53
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:04,420
He's doing okay, isn't he?

54
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:06,930
I assume you guys are still in touch?

55
00:05:08,540 --> 00:05:10,970
We don't talk that often.

56
00:05:11,830 --> 00:05:12,830
Fair enough.

57
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:14,300
You were just his tutor, after all.

58
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:21,600
Even though we live apart now,

59
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:24,290
he's never been the type to rely on me.

60
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:28,430
He's going to be a senior this year.

61
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:31,280
You should talk to him
about his exams and stuff.

62
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:38,050
Why don't you talk to him yourself?

63
00:05:38,770 --> 00:05:39,770
Huh?

64
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:42,860
He's probably got a lot
on his mind right now.

65
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:45,310
Hmm...?

66
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,110
Try acting like a big brother for once

67
00:05:50,740 --> 00:05:51,940
and show him some concern.

68
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:10,030
Oh, you're home.

69
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:12,520
Long time no see.

70
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:14,590
How've you been?

71
00:06:15,290 --> 00:06:16,290
Fine.

72
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,310
Don't you get lonely?

73
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:24,830
I'm used to it.

74
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,520
I see.

75
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:35,020
I was just over at Yoichi's place,

76
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,200
but he basically kicked me out.

77
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,360
Wait, why?

78
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:41,050
Did something happen?

79
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,610
No, nothing like that.

80
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:44,390
He's just worried about you.

81
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,580
He thought you might
be troubled by something

82
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,206
and told me to come check on you.

83
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:50,230
Oh...

84
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,490
Well, exams are coming up soon.

85
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,960
You can talk to me about anything.

86
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:04,410
I know, I'm being annoying, right?

87
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:07,190
Sorry for bothering you.

88
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:12,270
Hikaru, have you...

89
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:22,580
ever hurt someone who
was really important to you?

90
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,440
Yeah, I have.

91
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:31,230
Really?

92
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,510
I don't know if

93
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,280
regret is the right word...

94
00:07:37,393 --> 00:07:39,553
but I definitely thought,

95
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:42,060
"I wish I'd listened to
them more back then."

96
00:07:48,310 --> 00:07:51,820
I don't want you to have
those kinds of regrets.

97
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,800
Yeah...

98
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,079
Starting today,

99
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:09,180
construction for AC repairs
will begin in the 3rd-floor hallway.

100
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,640
If you're heading to Building B,
please use the 2nd-floor hallway.

101
00:08:13,770 --> 00:08:14,909
Got it!

102
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:15,810
(AC Maintenance Notice)

103
00:08:15,811 --> 00:08:18,931
(Location: Landing between 2nd and 3rd
floors, and near the 3rd-floor hallway.)

104
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,000
(DO NOT ENTER)

105
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,570
What should I do?

106
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,220
Senkawa?

107
00:08:57,470 --> 00:08:58,240
What's up?

108
00:08:58,241 --> 00:09:00,081
It's rare to see you over
by these classrooms.

109
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:02,050
Um...

110
00:09:03,370 --> 00:09:04,570
Is Kanata here?

111
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:06,470
Yeah, hold on a sec.

112
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,580
Kanata?

113
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:11,410
Oh, Kanata just stepped out.

114
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:12,680
Where'd he go?
No idea.

115
00:09:14,350 --> 00:09:15,350
The bathroom, maybe?

116
00:09:16,540 --> 00:09:17,540
Oh...

117
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,030
I'll come back later then.

118
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:20,650
Want me to go look for him?

119
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:22,610
No... it's okay.

120
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,860
Oh, you're back.

121
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,880
Yeah.

122
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,680
Senkawa was just here looking for you.

123
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,770
Oh... really?

124
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:56,250
You left your phone here,
so Mitsuki went to find you.

125
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,080
Wait, what?

126
00:09:59,020 --> 00:10:00,220
Oh, Mitsuki?

127
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,280
Kanata's back.

128
00:10:04,130 --> 00:10:05,130
Okay.

129
00:10:07,970 --> 00:10:09,940
She said she's going to bring Senkawa over.

130
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,260
Oh, I just remembered I
need to see the club advisor.

131
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,040
Seriously?

132
00:10:16,940 --> 00:10:18,540
That's such a lame way to avoid someone.

133
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,360
I don't know what's going on,

134
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:25,030
but you should probably just talk it out.

135
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,980
Wait, Kanata!

136
00:10:32,190 --> 00:10:33,190
Kanata!

137
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:35,250
Where are you going now?

138
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:37,750
Senkawa is on his way here.

139
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:44,020
Don't tell me...

140
00:10:44,730 --> 00:10:46,600
you guys still haven't made up?

141
00:10:51,010 --> 00:10:52,880
Did Akira say something to you?

142
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:56,060
No... I don't know the details.

143
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:59,070
But you two really need to talk...

144
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,249
I've been trying to talk to him!

145
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:02,250
Kanata!

146
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,620
Over here.

147
00:11:19,060 --> 00:11:19,970
Oh...

148
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:22,900
The whole class would
see us if we stayed there.

149
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,800
I'm sorry...

150
00:11:26,150 --> 00:11:27,500
Don't apologize.

151
00:11:28,010 --> 00:11:29,370
It's my fault.

152
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:47,920
No one should come by here.

153
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,600
So, what did you want to say?

154
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:05,130
About what I said after the match...

155
00:12:06,810 --> 00:12:09,030
when I told you it was
none of your business.

156
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,300
Oh...

157
00:12:16,380 --> 00:12:19,379
I was just... really emotional at the time.

158
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:20,380
I'm sorry.

159
00:12:20,650 --> 00:12:22,150
I must have looked pathetic, right?

160
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:24,870
What?

161
00:12:25,730 --> 00:12:26,830
You probably hate me now.

162
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,990
How could I ever hate
you for something like that?

163
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:33,990
Exactly.

164
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:39,900
It's not that easy to just hate someone.

165
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:48,300
So,

166
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:50,830
don't be afraid. Just talk to me.

167
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:54,000
Maybe if you say it out loud,

168
00:12:54,090 --> 00:12:55,750
it'll start to make sense.

169
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,260
But...

170
00:13:05,470 --> 00:13:06,470
And besides,

171
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:11,420
it's too late to tell me

172
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:13,320
not to like you.

173
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:16,810
You're all I can think about.

174
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:20,470
My head is a complete mess.

175
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:44,100
Back in middle school...

176
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:49,150
I went to a different prep school

177
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,370
than the one I go to now.

178
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:58,380
And there,

179
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:01,150
I met this guy I was pretty close with.

180
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:04,250
I heard Nakamura got a girlfriend.

181
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:06,710
Oh, really?

182
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:10,420
I don't even want a girlfriend.

183
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,710
It seems like such a hassle.

184
00:14:14,820 --> 00:14:15,820
Besides,

185
00:14:16,310 --> 00:14:17,950
I've got you, Akira.

186
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:23,930
Oh.

187
00:14:24,490 --> 00:14:25,490
Wait.

188
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:27,090
Akira, do you have a crush on someone?

189
00:14:27,490 --> 00:14:28,490
Uh...

190
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:30,010
No way, seriously?

191
00:14:30,210 --> 00:14:31,210
No, it's not...

192
00:14:31,350 --> 00:14:32,020
Who is it?
Someone from prep school?

193
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:33,900
Or from your regular school?

194
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:45,020
I was thinking, if it were a guy,

195
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:47,140
maybe...

196
00:14:47,950 --> 00:14:49,310
it wouldn't be such a hassle.

197
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:50,860
Huh?

198
00:14:50,970 --> 00:14:51,970
What?

199
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:53,590
I mean,

200
00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:56,480
you could just be like friends,

201
00:14:58,240 --> 00:15:01,120
and it would be more fun to date, right?

202
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,840
What?

203
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,260
That's literally impossible.

204
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,370
Wait, what?

205
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:16,189
Don't tell me you're into...

206
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:17,820
No, it's not like that!

207
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:20,360
I was just wondering

208
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:22,840
if anyone else felt that way.

209
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:25,900
There's no way anyone would feel like that.

210
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,480
That's so gross.

211
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:38,590
After that... I tried to
laugh it off as a joke,

212
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:43,960
but he started giving me a hard time.

213
00:15:49,283 --> 00:15:52,053
The way he treated me completely changed.

214
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:06,270
Was that when Kanda-san

215
00:16:09,310 --> 00:16:10,310
became your tutor?

216
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:13,970
Yeah.

217
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:19,840
My brother introduced us.

218
00:16:23,130 --> 00:16:26,030
After a while, Kanda-san asked
why I stopped going to prep school.

219
00:16:31,010 --> 00:16:32,740
That's when I realized that he also...

220
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,840
liked guys.

221
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:44,270
It's like you were both just
seeking comfort in each other.

222
00:16:46,330 --> 00:16:47,330
Yeah.

223
00:16:50,592 --> 00:16:51,822
Because I was weak.

224
00:17:00,740 --> 00:17:03,050
I don't know what
Kanda-san was going through,

225
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:09,610
but I know he was someone
you really needed to lean on.

226
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:15,080
But I...

227
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:17,980
That guy,

228
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:22,810
the one who did that to
you... I'll never forgive him.

229
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,370
I guess it couldn't be helped.

230
00:17:29,970 --> 00:17:31,760
Everyone has things
they just can't accept.

231
00:17:34,716 --> 00:17:37,076
What makes someone
uncomfortable is different for everyone.

232
00:17:39,670 --> 00:17:41,070
That's not necessarily a bad thing.

233
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,330
But that's no excuse for bullying.

234
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,320
Even if you don't understand someone,

235
00:17:47,990 --> 00:17:49,800
you shouldn't do things to hurt them.

236
00:17:52,770 --> 00:17:54,010
I don't want my existence

237
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:59,080
to cause any more trouble for you.

238
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:03,000
The friendship

239
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:06,220
he once felt for me...

240
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,450
turned sour so easily.

241
00:18:22,370 --> 00:18:24,040
I'm not like him.

242
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:30,240
I know.

243
00:18:33,620 --> 00:18:35,250
But I'm just so scared.

244
00:18:39,710 --> 00:18:41,360
Whether it's falling for someone

245
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:46,500
or having dreams for the future.

246
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:54,780
I can't control how I feel,

247
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:03,010
but I don't want you to
just accept how I am either.

248
00:19:09,122 --> 00:19:10,330
That's my answer.

249
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:35,380
I'm home.

250
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:37,020
Oh.

251
00:19:37,410 --> 00:19:39,050
Feels like I haven't seen you in forever.

252
00:19:39,650 --> 00:19:41,090
Well, I was away for the tournament.

253
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:42,550
Here, a souvenir.

254
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:44,170
Thanks.

255
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:45,850
Oh, right.

256
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,410
I got you something too.

257
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:54,770
Thank you.

258
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:02,430
By the way, Hikaru...

259
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:06,580
Did you have a fight with your girlfriend?

260
00:20:09,460 --> 00:20:10,460
What?

261
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:12,350
No, I just thought...

262
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:13,900
you seemed...

263
00:20:14,070 --> 00:20:15,380
different.

264
00:20:17,230 --> 00:20:18,560
Mind your own business.

265
00:20:19,070 --> 00:20:20,270
Alright, go back to your room.

266
00:20:21,610 --> 00:20:22,460
Go on.
Okay, okay.

267
00:20:50,660 --> 00:20:55,450
I'm really sorry for not
replying to your texts.

268
00:20:56,510 --> 00:20:58,280
No, it's totally fine.

269
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:02,120
More importantly,

270
00:21:04,110 --> 00:21:05,910
are you sure you're
okay seeing me right now?

271
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:10,110
Yeah...

272
00:21:13,010 --> 00:21:14,010
I see...

273
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:23,390
I...

274
00:21:25,170 --> 00:21:26,170
I used to think that...

275
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:30,850
even if things didn't work out with Kanata,

276
00:21:32,310 --> 00:21:34,680
it would be okay as long as I had you.

277
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,260
I see.

278
00:21:39,780 --> 00:21:41,080
I kept telling myself

279
00:21:41,850 --> 00:21:44,700
that you were just using
me as an escape too.

280
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:50,040
The closer I got to Kanata,

281
00:21:52,097 --> 00:21:53,577
the more I used you as a shield.

282
00:21:56,180 --> 00:21:57,430
That's not true.

283
00:22:00,810 --> 00:22:02,010
If anything,

284
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:06,480
I'm the one who should
apologize for being so immature.

285
00:22:10,130 --> 00:22:11,130
But,

286
00:22:13,030 --> 00:22:14,640
I was only thinking about myself.

287
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:20,920
I didn't consider your feelings at all.

288
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:29,090
I think I was just...

289
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:33,290
really envious of you.

290
00:22:44,907 --> 00:22:46,367
If you can express your feelings,

291
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:49,330
it's better to just say them.

292
00:22:53,780 --> 00:22:54,880
Kanda-san...

293
00:22:58,490 --> 00:23:00,500
While Hikaru is back,

294
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,680
I'll come over to your
place to hang out again.

295
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,730
Is that okay?

296
00:23:09,060 --> 00:23:10,160
Of course it is.

297
00:23:12,340 --> 00:23:16,250
You're my brother's best friend, after all.

298
00:23:19,870 --> 00:23:20,870
Oh, right.

299
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:22,580
I almost forgot.

300
00:23:25,890 --> 00:23:26,990
My brother...

301
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,630
said you kicked him out,

302
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,440
and he seemed pretty bummed about it.

303
00:23:31,950 --> 00:23:33,280
He's exaggerating.

304
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:34,470
No, he really was.

305
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:43,450
How long are you two going to keep this up?

306
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:45,220
Huh?

307
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,780
Keep what up?

308
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:50,590
Just make up with him already.

309
00:23:51,030 --> 00:23:52,030
What?

310
00:23:52,876 --> 00:23:55,879
It's so awkward, being
around you two like this.

311
00:23:57,901 --> 00:24:02,250
If you keep sulking like you did when you quit
the soccer club, what are you going to do?

312
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:11,750
Are you just going to run away again?

313
00:24:18,250 --> 00:24:19,250
Oh, for heaven's sake...

314
00:24:19,470 --> 00:24:20,470
Fine.

315
00:24:31,490 --> 00:24:32,490
Come with me.

316
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:35,680
Wait.

317
00:24:41,950 --> 00:24:42,750
Kanata,

318
00:24:42,810 --> 00:24:43,810
where are you going?

319
00:24:44,570 --> 00:24:46,050
Class is about to start.

320
00:25:04,510 --> 00:25:05,510
I've...

321
00:25:07,050 --> 00:25:09,330
never skipped class before.

322
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:11,900
Neither have I.

323
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:19,590
But I've

324
00:25:20,610 --> 00:25:21,710
already made up my mind.

325
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:25,380
Huh?

326
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:17,440
(Final Episode Preview)
Once blurred and wavering,

327
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,690
we now have clear silhouettes,

328
00:26:20,170 --> 00:26:21,430
and different colors,

329
00:26:21,870 --> 00:26:23,010
slowly blending together.

330
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,770
So we don't lose what's real,

331
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:28,570
so we don't lose our way.

